ds Carpenter Pass for .2 km to a junction. Turn left and pass a yoga platform in a meadow below Misty Peak.<\/span><br \/>\n<span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;\">0.7km Reach a junction: Right takes a higher trail side hilling across some avalanche paths, but with views. Left follows a lower trail in the woods.<\/span><br \/>\n<span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;\">1.4 km. Descend towards Cody Pass via switchbacks. The high and low trails merge again. Ascend the other side of Cody Pass. On the top of the ridge are the oddly shaped larches called the \u201cTroll Trees\u201d. Descend slightly to reach lower Motherlode Lake. The trail fades into a marked cairn route up a grassy ramp to Upper Motherlode Lake at 4.3 km.<\/span><br \/>\n<span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;\">Carlyle Lodge has one of their backcountry campsites \u2013 part of the Sourdough Traverse \u2013 at this lake.<\/span><\/p>\n<p><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;\"><strong>What to Do:<\/strong> Continue along the trailed Sourdough Traverse as long as desired. It is only about 16 km to Idaho Peak.<\/span><\/p>\n","protected":false},"excerpt":{"rendered":"<p>This trail extends from Carlyle Pass and the nearby Carlyle Lodge west along Silver Ridge. Larches are a highlight in the fall. Rating:\u00a0\u2666\u2666\u2666\u2666\u25ca Location: At the remote headwaters of Carpenter Creek above Cody and Sandon. Difficulty: B1 moderate Elevation Gain: &hellip; <a href=\"https:\/\/www.ronperrier.net\/2020\/08\/16\/motherlode-lakes\/\">Continue reading <span class=\"meta-nav\">&rarr;<\/span><\/a><\/p>\n","protected":false},"author":1,"featured_media":0,"comment_status":"closed","ping_status":"closed","sticky":false,"template":"","format":"standard","meta":{"jetpack_post_was_ever_published":false,"_jetpack_newsletter_access":"","_jetpack_dont_email_post_to_subs":false,"_jetpack_newsletter_tier_id":0,"_jetpack_memberships_contains_pay